Our hypersonic tech combines the speed of ballistic missiles and the agility of cruise missiles. Link in bio. #NorthropGrumman :airplane_selector:"

b'After more than 230 days in orbit our NG-11 Cygnus spacecraft successfully concluded its cargo resupply mission to the @iss. After delivering nearly 8,000 pounds of cargo to the station, Cygnus departed and remained in orbit showcasing its ability to host payloads for experiments and technology demonstrations. Along with being the first long-duration flight, this mission also marked the first time two Cygnus vehicles were in orbit at the same time. The NG-12 mission, launched in November, and NG-11 were both controlled from our Mission Operations Center in Dulles, VA. Stay tuned for updates on our next Cygnus mission, NG-13! #NorthropGrumman'
